bug.short_desc: more.jsp garbles matches on lines crossing internal JFlex buffer boundary

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 4254 file that demonstrates the problem
If there's a match on a line that crosses the internal JFlex buffer boundary, more.jsp fails to show the matching line correctly.
For example, index the attached file buffer_boundary.txt and search for "boundary". The following result will be displayed:
1 JFlex has default buffer size 16384. Construct a file with a line that crosses that boundary. 5 The lines above contain about 16365 characters, so this line should cross the boundary. [all...]
Then click the [all...] link, and see the following results:
1 JFlex has default buffer size 16384. Construct a file with a line that crosses that boundary. 5 boundary. 22834 Here's a line at the end, also containing the word boundary...
Note that the match at line 5 now only shows one word, whereas it should have shown the entire line.

This happens because PlainLineTokenizer.holdOn() uses the JFlex-internal field zzStartRead, which becomes meaningless once the buffer boundary is passed.
Bug #15938 is logged to make PlainLineTokenizer.lex stop using JFlex's internal fields, so a fix for that bug may help.
